claim.claim-text:
1. An optical to wireless converter receiving one or more optical channels modulated at optical carrier frequencies and providing one or more modulated wireless data channels modulated at different wireless carrier frequencies, said converter comprising: 
a channelizer receiving the one or more optical channels and producing one or more extracted optical carrier signals; 
an optical frequency shifter receiving the one or more extracted optical carrier signals and producing one or more frequency-shifted extracted optical carrier signals; 
an optical heterodyne detector receiving the one or more frequency-shifted extracted optical carrier signals and the one or more optical channels and producing the one or more modulated wireless channels.

28. The optical to wireless converter according to claim 27, wherein the optical heterodyne detector comprises: 
a first optical coupler receiving the composite optical signal and the composite frequency-shifted extracted optical carrier signal; 
a second optical coupler receiving the composite extracted optical carrier signal and the composite frequency-shifted extracted optical carrier signal; 
a first optical switch receiving a first optical output from the first optical coupler; 
a second optical switch receiving a second optical output from the second optical coupler; 
a photodetector receiving a switched output from the first optical switch and a switched optical output from the second optical switch.

58. The optical to wireless converter according to claim 57, wherein the step of optically heterodyning the composite optical signal, the composite extracted optical carrier signal and the composite frequency-shifted extracted optical carrier signal comprises: 
coupling the composite optical signal and the composite frequency-shifted extracted optical carrier signal to produce a first coupled optical signal; 
coupling the composite extracted optical carrier signal and the composite frequency-shifted extracted optical carrier signal to produce a second coupled optical signal; 
selectably switching the first coupled optical signal or the second coupled optical signal to a photodetector; 
generating the wireless data channels with the photodetector when the first coupled optical signal is switched to the photodetector; and 
generating the one or more unmodulated wireless carrier signals with the photodetector when the second coupled optical signal is switched to the photodetector.

61. A converter for converting one or more optical channels from an optical wavelength division multiplexed network to one or more wireless channels in a one-to-one correspondence between the optical channels and the wireless channels, the one or more optical channels being combined in a composite optical signal having optical energy and the wireless channels being modulated at different wireless carrier frequencies, the converter comprising: 
a wavelength division demultiplexer receiving a portion of the optical energy of the composite optical signal and producing one or more demultiplexed optical channels; 
a channelizer receiving the one or more separate demultiplexed optical channels and producing one or more extracted optical carrier signals having optical energy, each extracted optical carrier signal of the one or more extracted optical carrier signals corresponding to a different optical channel of the one or more optical channels; 
a first optical combiner receiving a portion of the optical energy of each extracted optical carrier signal, the first optical combiner forming a composite extracted optical carrier signal; 
an optical frequency converter receiving a portion of the optical energy of each extracted optical carrier signal, the optical frequency converter generating one or more frequency-shifted extracted optical carrier signals, wherein the optical frequency converter shifts each extracted optical carrier signal by a frequency of one of the different wireless carrier frequencies to form the one or more frequency-shifted extracted optical carrier signals; 
a second optical combiner receiving the one or more frequency-shifted extracted optical carrier signals to form a composite frequency-shifted extracted optical carrier signal; 
an optical-heterodyne detector receiving the composite optical signal, the composite extracted optical carrier signal, and the composite frequency-shifted extracted optical carrier signal, the optical-heterodyne detector producing the wireless channels at the different wireless carrier frequencies.

65. The converter of claim 61, wherein the optical frequency converter comprises a plurality of frequency converter units, at least one frequency converter unit of the plurality of frequency converter units comprising: 
a pump laser; 
an optical coupler; 
an ER-doped fiber amplifier; and 
a semiconductor optical amplifier.

79. A method for filtering a composite optical signal containing a plurality of modulated optical data signals to extract a plurality of unmodulated optical carriers, the method comprising the steps of: 
demultiplexing the composite optical signal to generate one or more demultiplexed optical data signals; 
coupling each demultiplexed optical data signal of the one or more demultiplexed optical data signals to a corresponding microsphere of an array of microspheres; 
perturbing the corresponding microsphere to have resonance at or near an optical carrier frequency of the demultiplexed optical data signal coupled to the microsphere; and 
coupling one unmodulated optical carrier of the plurality of unmodulated optical carriers from the microsphere.
